# üé® UI/UX Skills --- README

This repository contains my clean notes on **UI/UX design
fundamentals**, written in a simple and human-friendly way.\
These are the concepts I follow when designing interfaces for web apps,
dashboards, and modern digital products.

## üß† What is UI/UX?

**UI (User Interface)** ‚Üí How the product **looks**\
**UX (User Experience)** ‚Üí How the product **feels & works**

Great design = **Beautiful + Simple + Fast + Intuitive**

# üéØ UI (User Interface) Skills

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Visual Hierarchy

Make it easy for users to know what matters most. - Bigger text = more
important\
- Use spacing to separate content\
- Use color to highlight key actions\
- Keep the layout clean

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Color Theory

Colors set the mood and guide actions. - Use 1 main color + 1
secondary + neutrals\
- Avoid too many colors\
- Ensure good contrast for readability\
- Use consistent colors for states (success, danger, warning)

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Typography

Readable text = enjoyable experience. - Use max **2 font families**\
- Line height: 1.4--1.6\
- Use weight (bold/medium) for hierarchy\
- Avoid small fonts (\< 14px)

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Components & Consistency

Design in systems, not isolated screens. - Buttons should follow one
style\
- Spacing should follow a scale (4px / 8px)\
- Use consistent radii, shadows, and icons\
- Maintain uniform padding across components

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ Layout & Grids

Structure makes UI predictable. - Use 12-column grid\
- Maintain even spacing\
- Group related elements\
- Avoid cramped edges

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ Iconography

Icons should be: - Simple\
- Consistent in stroke width\
- Easy to understand\
- Used sparingly

# üåü UX (User Experience) Skills

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ User Flows

Plan how users move through your product. - Keep steps logical\
- Remove unnecessary actions\
- Make navigation intuitive\
- Reduce friction

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Simplicity

The best designs have fewer distractions. - One main action per screen\
- Simple labels\
- Short forms\
- Clear instructions

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Feedback & Interaction

Every action should create reaction. - Hover + click feedback\
- Helpful error messages\
- Loading states\
- Success confirmations

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Accessibility (A11Y)

Make designs usable for everyone. - High contrast\
- Alt text for images\
- Keyboard navigation\
- Clear focus indicators

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ Responsive Design

Adapts gracefully across screens. - Mobile ‚Üí Tablet ‚Üí Desktop\
- Flexible layouts\
- Responsive text sizes\
- Logical rearrangement

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ Usability Testing

Feedback reveals problems. - Observe user navigation\
- Identify hesitation points\
- Improve based on feedback

# üß± UI/UX Principles

-   Don't make users think\
-   Clear over clever\
-   Consistency builds trust\
-   Reduce cognitive load\
-   Every element must have purpose\
-   Design for accessibility first

